    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="251"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Stoeckl</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-03-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 3, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your communication of the 5–17th ultimo, in relation to the reservation by
                    General Davis, commanding the United States military forces in Alaska, of a
                    certain portion of the town of New Archangel for the use of this government, and
                    suggesting on your part a purchase of the buildings thereon.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to state that, upon the information now in possession
                    of this department, the property in question would appear to have vested in the
                    United States under the treaty of March 30, 1867.</p>
                <p>If, however, the fact be otherwise, I find, upon consultation with the Secretary
                    of the Treasury, that there is not at present such occasion for the use of the
                    buildings as to recommend the purchase of them by this government.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, a renewed assurance of my highest consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward de Stoeckl, &amp;c</hi>., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
